bes one ethno-cultural community, discussing such issues as childbirth, mental illness, dental care, hospitalization, and death, as well as home country culture, common reasons for emigrating, and challenges in adjusting to a new culture. This new edition provides up-to-date statistics and fresh analysis, responding to changing trends in immigration. Additional material includes a new chapter addressing the special circumstances of refugees; short real-life stories of immigrants' and refugees' experiences; and a thorough, easy-to-use index.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSocial medicine. 0aTranscultural medical carezCanadavHandbooks, manuals, etc. 7aMEDICAL / Nursing / Nurse & Patient.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Joan M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnderson, Joan M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAnhaouy, Chansokhy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAssanand, Shashi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBehjati-Sabet, Afsaneh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChambers, Natalie A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChambers, Natalie A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDias, Maud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDinh, Dai-Kha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGanesan, Soma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGleave, Danica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerbert, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirkham, Sheryl Reimer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKobayashi, Karen, eco